#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Queue ko array se implement karna hai.
- front pointer batayega kis index se remove karna hai.
- rear pointer batayega kis index par next insertion hoga.
- Push -> rear par insert.
- Pop -> front se remove.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. Initially front = 0, rear = 0.
2. Push(x):
   - arr[rear] par x daalo.
   - rear++.
3. Pop():
   - Agar front == rear, queue empty hai → return -1.
   - arr[front] store karo.
   - front++.
   - Stored value return karo.

📝 EXAMPLE

Operations:
push(2)
push(3)
pop()
push(4)
pop()

Initially:
front=0, rear=0

push(2)
[2]
front=0, rear=1

push(3)
[2,3]
front=0, rear=2

pop()
remove arr[0] = 2
front=1, rear=2

Queue => [3]

push(4)
[2,3,4]
front=1, rear=3

Actual Queue => [3,4]

pop()
remove arr[1] = 3
front=2, rear=3

Remaining Queue => [4]

❓ WHY ARRAY + TWO POINTERS
- Array elements store karne ke liye.
- front tracks next element to remove.
- rear tracks next position to insert.
- No shifting of elements needed.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Time  : O(1) Push
Time  : O(1) Pop
Space : O(N)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Queue empty condition => front == rear.
- Push always rear par hota hai.
- Pop always front se hota hai.
- Element delete nahi karte, sirf front aage badha dete hain.
- FIFO maintain hota hai because insertion rear se aur removal front se hota hai.

#Code:

class MyQueue {
    int front;
    int rear;
    int arr[] = new int[100005];

    MyQueue() {
        front = 0;
        rear = 0;
    }

    void push(int a) {
      //You can code here
      //checking if it is full or not
      if(rear == arr.length){
        return;
      }
      arr[rear] = a;
      rear++;
      return;
    }

    int pop() {
      //You can code here
      //Checking if it is empty or not
      if(front == rear){
        return -1;
      }

      int temp = arr[front];
      front++;
      return temp;

    }
}
